 service can help you to diagnose the exact cause of the problem and suggest the best.";i:17;s:62:"Why is my garage door making a loud noise every time i use it.";i:18;s:101:"Loud noises when a garage door is being operated can be either be the door itself or the door opener.";i:19;s:55:"You have to figure out where your noise is coming from.";i:20;s:115:"This can be easily done by disconnecting the opener from the door and operating door manually without using opener.";i:21;s:53:"If the door still makes the same loud noises than it.";i:22;s:41:"Lubricate or Replace Garage Door Springs.";i:23;s:85:"A common culprit for loud garage doors is the springs located at the top of the door.";i:24;s:55:"You need to lubricate the springs several times a year.";i:25;s:67:"However remember the extreme tension the torsion springs are under.";i:26;s:98:"Other than a vehicle a garage door opener is probably the most prominent noise source in a garage.";i:27;s:89:"They are strong motors that often introduce a large amount of vibration into a structure.";i:28;s:69:"Depending on the location of the garage this can be quite bothersome.";i:29;s:80:"The situation below illustrates a bit more challenging of a situation than most.";i:30;s:150:"According to Home Guide a garage door opener repair cost ranges from 100 190 plus partsIt also depends on the type of opener where you live and fixes.";i:31;s:78:"Now garage door opener replacement and installation can range from 150 to 550.";i:32;s:113:"Having a failing garage door opener can be bothersome yet it likewise affects the safety of your family and pets.";i:33;s:113:"Your garage door may also be noisy because the insulation strip on the bottom of the door is worn out or missing.";i:34;s:137:"With a missing insulation strip you will feel cold and wet coming into your garage and hear a loud banging noise when the door is closed.";i:35;s:78:"Noise can also be caused by the garage door hitting the cement floor too hard.";i:36;s:133:"A loud garage door opener that makes a lot of noise is for some people a slight nuisance and for others a reason to wake up at night.";i:37;s:47:"Some garage door motors are louder than others.";i:38;s:76:"Noise levels depend mostly on drive-style gear assembly and operating speed.";i:39;s:41:"Old garage door openers can be very loud.";i:40;s:66:"If yours is more than 20 years old it might be time to replace it.";i:41;s:87:"Use a metal lubricant such as 10W30 motor oil to lubricate all of the doors components.";i:42;s:75:"Lubricate PVC parts like the weatherstripping on the exterior frame with a.";i:43;s:39:"How to Stop a Noisy Garage Door Opener.";i:44;s:82:"Vibration is the cause of most noise problems associated with garage door openers.";i:45;s:66:"Vibration transfers through the steel framework of the opener and.";i:46;s:147:"Ts great having the convenience of an automatic garage door but when it decides to become noisy the thought of that convenience quickly disappears.";i:47;s:84:"Noisy garage doors are disruptive and can be a sign that things are not quite right.";i:48;s:75:"Here are a few things you could try to help with those rattles and squeaks.";i:49;s:105:"Throw in an extremely noisy garage and you will find your grumpy-self taking over more than you wish for.";i:50;s:141:"A squeaking and screeching garage door opening at 5am on a daily basis is enough to make anyone go crazy including your next-door neighbours.";i:51;s:113:"Before my garage door was fine until it closed all the way at which point it slammed into the ground very loudly.";i:52;s:58:"I adjusted the limiter dials until it closed much quieter.";i:53;s:108:"Since then and over the last few months it makes an equally loud noise now when I initiate an open or close.";i:54;s:114:"A noisy garage door happens because a problem exists among one or more of the many parts that connect it together.";i:55;s:164:"If thats the case then garage door repair is on the horizon though it can be very helpful to know prior to the start of that fix whats making the garage door noisy.";i:56;s:32:"Below are some of those reasons.";i:57;s:86:"Hang the motor from the mounting straps on the garage door opener using rubber pieces.";i:58;s:55:"Suspend the opener from the frame by the rubber pieces.";i:59;s:93:"The rubber will absorb noisy vibrations before they cause the metal support frame to shudder.";i:60;s:75:"Test the garage door and opener to make sure that they still work properly.";i:61;s:105:"Noisy appliances can be a very annoying especially when it is something that you tend to use quite often.";i:62;s:114:"Noisy automatic garage doors are an example of such situations as you use the garage every day to get to your car.";i:63;s:94:"Dont worry its not a serious issue and you can fix it yourself without calling a professional.";i:64;s:40:"As you can hear the motor is very noisy.";i:65;s:79:"Is it so loud your neighbors a lot of the noise during operation can come from.";}}